sentences: Grae Cameron Garcia Fernandez (born November 7, 2001) is a Filipino teen actor, host and recording artist, known as one of the vocalists of Star Magic's teen boy-group Gimme 5.
Fernandez was born on November 7, 2001 in Manila, Philippines.

In December 2013, Fernandez joined the boy-group Gimme 5 - a band formed by ABS-CBN's Star Magic along with teenstar Nash Aguas as leader, Joaquin Lucas Reyes, Brace Henry Arquiza and John Emmanuel Bermundo.
Gimme 5 released their self-titled debut album in November 2014 under Star Music.

In August 2014, Fernandez started his acting career as a cast member of "Perfecto" an episode in fantasy-drama, comedy anthology Wansapanataym  which is produced and aired by ABS-CBN every Saturdays and Sundays.
Fernandez was then cast in a special participation as one of the young characters in the 2015 Primetime TV series Bridges of Love.
In August 2015, Fernandez made his film debut  as one of the supporting cast in a certified box-office hit movie The Love Affair top-billed by Richard Gomez, Dawn Zulueta and Bea Alonzo.
Fernandez first appeared on TV in a 2013 Jollibee Summer Bucket Treats commercial.
He made his television debut on the ABS-CBN game show Minute
The following year, the group held a series of TV guestings and mall shows to promote their album.
The group kicked off their "Gimme5 Best Summer Ever" album tour a few weeks ago.
